ze/ ''Eyes on the Prize'' Series]\n*[http://www.facinghistory.org/campus/reslib.nsf/sub/onlinecampus/publications/studyguides/eyesontheprize Teacher study guide]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20041208030537/http://pbsvideodb.pbs.org/resources/eyes/ PBS Lesson Plans]\n*[http://digital.wustl.edu/e/eop/index.html ''Eyes on the Prize'' Interview Transcripts], Washington University Library\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20090710154007/http://library.wustl.edu/units/spec/filmandmedia/collections/henry-hampton-collection/eyes_on_the_prize.html ''Eyes on the Prize I'' - Henry Hampton Collection], Washington University's Film and Media Archive\n*[http://library.wustl.edu/units/spec/filmandmedia/collections/henry-hampton-collection/eyes_on_the_prize_2.html ''Eyes on the Prize II'' - Henry Hampton Collection], Washington University's Film and Media Archive\n*{{IMDb title|id=0092999|title=Eyes On the Prize}}\n*{{IMDb title|id=0233051|title=Eyes On the Prize II}}\n\n{{American Experience}}\n{{Civil rights movement|state=collapsed}}\n{{TCA Award for Program of the Year}}\n{{TCA Award for Outstanding Achievement in News and Information}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Eyes On The Prize}}\n[[Category:1987 in American television]]\n[[Category:Civil rights movement in television]]\n[[Category:1980s American documentary television series]]\n[[Category:1990s American documentary television series]]\n[[Category:American Experience]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about African Americans]]\n[[Category:Documentary films about the civil rights movement]]\n[[Category:Historical television series]]\n[[Category:Civil rights movement]]\n[[Category:Peabody Award-winning television programs]]\n", "name_user": "Ryn AAPB", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eSee also:Adding Eyes on the Prize archival materials contributed to the American Archive of Public Broadcasting.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eyes_on_the_Prize"}
